race.comment: MR FERRARI (11) went forward last start and gave a great sight when second over 1300m at Bordertown. Should be prominent despite the wide draw. Bold showing expected again. ROKABYE WARRIOR (5) met with solid support last time out but couldn't meet expectation in a disappointing performance. Can get things back on track this time. LIMBERING (12) was far from her best last time at Horsham but is capable of a much better showing this time. Is a winner over this track and trip and is drawn to advantage. Good luck reeling her in under the lightweight if she gets it her own way in front. AQUAHOLIC (1) should be peaking fourth run from a spell.
